RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 13600. FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 15, 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCK CITY ROCKET tracked the top pair along the inside into the turn, tipped two wide heading into upper stretch, edged up closer then given cue at the eighth pole, reached the leader in deep stretch and edged away. LANGUAGE BARRIER broke out at the start and sped to the lead, set the pace and held clear around the turn, saved ground entering the lane, sustained bid along the inside and failed to hold off the winner in final stages. BARSTOW got pushed out a couple paths at the start and raced off the early leaders, picked up the pace three wide around the turn, swung four paths wide into upper stretch and ran on for a share. FEROCITY was forwardly placed and sat just off the pacesetter around the turn, hustled along three wide into the stretch run and weakened in the final furlong. UNCLE CHAD lacked speed and raced in the back, swung five wide into stretch and failed to rally.

ENTRY.NAME: Language Barrier
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, sustained inside bid, edged late

ENTRY.NAME: Rock City Rocket
ENTRY.COMMENT: track top pair, rail turn, 2wd into stretch, cue 1/8p, edged away

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 13600. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIR DEPUTY sped to the lead and crossed over to the inside soon after the start, held clear around the turn, saved ground turning for home and kept to task in hand. TOUGH COMPANY stalked the leader into the turn, hustled up two wide near the quarter pole, was no match for clear winner but sustained a steady bid and secured second best. A. K. SAFARI raced off the early pace, picked up the tempo four wide approaching the quarter pole, swung four wide into the lane and prevailed for a share. BOTTOMLESS lacked speed and raced in the back, saved ground around the turn, was ridden along the rail into upper stretch and had no kick. LIBERTARIAN tracked the pace in the opening quarter, hustled along in contention around the turn then gave way. PRICE TO PAY raced up close through the backstretch, weakened mid-way around the turn and continued to tire in the drive.
